'''Robin Alexander E. Shroot''' (born 26 March 1988) is an [[England|English]]-born [[association football|football]]er who plays for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] as a [[midfielder]]. He made his first-team debut in the [[FA Cup]] third round match against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.]] in January 2009. He has represented [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|Northern Ireland at under-21]] level.

==Club career==
Shroot was born in [[London]]. He began his football career as an eight-year-old with [[Wimbledon F.C.|Wimbledon]], remaining with the club until released at 16.<ref name=Mercury20090110/><ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.mkdons.com/page/TeamTemplate4/0,,10420~276933,00.html 
|title=Six Wins Out Of Seven Against 'The Palace' 
|publisher=[[MK Dons F.C.]] 
|date=24 September 2002 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
He then joined [[Staines Town F.C.|Staines Town]]'s academy, which operated in association with [[Kingston College (England)|Kingston College]].<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.stainesmassive.co.uk/academy.html 
|title=Academy 
|publisher=[[Staines Town F.C.]] 
|accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref> He scored the only goal in the 2006 Middlesex Premier Cup final, the first time the club had even reached the final,<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.stainesmassive.co.uk/News/newsmar06.html 
|title=News Mar 06: Young Swans bring home the silverware 
|publisher=[[Staines Town F.C.]] 
|first=Steve |last=Parsons 
|date=15 March 2006 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
and contributed to the side reaching the Southern Youth League championship play-off and (as Kingston College) the final of the [[English Schools' Football Association]] U-18 Colleges' Trophy.<ref name=StainesMay06>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.stainesmassive.co.uk/News/newsmay06.html 
|title=News May 06 
|publisher=[[Staines Town F.C.]] 
|accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.esfa.co.uk/competitions/fixture.asp?view=2005,Boys,u18_ct#round8 
|title=ESFA Under 18 Colleges' Trophy 2005&ndash;2006 
|publisher=[[English Schools' Football Association]] 
|date=4 April 2007 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref> 
Shroot never played for Staines' [[Isthmian League Premier Division]] team, though he was an occasional unused [[substitute (football)|substitute]],<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.stainesmassive.co.uk/News/newsjan06.html 
|title=News Jan 06 
|publisher=[[Staines Town F.C.]] 
|accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref> and scored in the final as the club won the Southern Combination Cup, a first-team competition.<ref name=StainesMay06/>

In September 2006, Shroot joined [[AFC Wimbledon]], also of the Isthmian League Premier. The club described him as a "skilful ball-playing winger who likes to take on opponents and deliver telling crosses".<ref name="AFCW Profile"/> He made his league debut, showing "plenty of promise" as he played the first 65 minutes of the 2&ndash;1 win at [[Ashford Town F.C. (Middlesex)|Ashford Town (Middlesex)]] on 26 September 2006.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/-/reports/ryman-league-premier-division/8960/ashford-town-middlesex 
|title=Match report | Ashford Town (Middlesex) vs. AFC Wimbledon (26th September 2006) 
|publisher=[[AFC Wimbledon]] 
|date=26 September 2006 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
In the 2006&ndash;07 season he made two starts and five substitute appearances in the league without scoring.<ref name="AFCW Profile">{{cite web 
|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/players.php?Psection_id=3&Psub_section_id=3&apps=1&player_id=1044&squad=1&position=Midfielder 
|title=Robin Shroot 
|publisher=[[AFC Wimbledon]] 
|accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
In November 2007, Shroot joined [[Harrow Borough F.C.|Harrow Borough]], also of the Isthmian League Premier, on loan, initially for a month. He made his debut on 10 November 2007 in a 2&ndash;1 defeat at [[Margate F.C.|Margate]].<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.harrowboro.com/matchrep.php?typ=mch&id=209 
|title=Match details: Margate 2&ndash;1 Harrow 
|publisher=[[Harrow Borough F.C.]] 
|date=10 November 2007 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
His spell with Harrow was extended to three months,<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.surreycomet.co.uk/news/1901613.shroots_not_coming_home_to_dons/ 
|title=Shroot's not coming home to Dons 
|work=Surrey Comet |publisher=[[Newsquest]] 
|first=Sami |last=Mokbel |date=13 December 2007 
|accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref> though disrupted by injury,<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.harrowboro.com/matchrep.php?typ=mch&id=219 
|title=Match details: Leyton 0&ndash;3 Harrow 
|publisher=[[Harrow Borough F.C.]] 
|date=12 January 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
and brought him six league goals from ten games. Shroot finished the 2007&ndash;08 season with another six league goals for AFC Wimbledon from five starts and seven substitute appearances,<ref name="AFCW Profile"/> contributing to the club's [[promotion and relegation|promotion]] to the [[Conference South]]. Shroot's contract expired at the end of that season. The club made him an offer which he chose not to accept, so he became available for transfer;<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news.php?Psection_id=2&Psub_section_id=2&op=archive&monthID=5&yearID=2008 
|title=Archived news: June 2008: Robin Shroot to move on 
|publisher=[[AFC Wimbledon]] 
|date=12 June 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
manager Terry Brown felt that the player's representatives did not want him to stay with the club.<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.wimbledonguardian.co.uk/sport/football/afcwimbledon/3981627.Brown_mulls_over_the_one_that_got_away/ 
|title=Dons boss still regrets Shroot departure 
|work=Wimbledon Guardian |publisher=[[Newsquest]] 
|first=Simon |last=Fitzjohn 
|date=16 December 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>

Under the [[Bosman ruling]], because of the player's age, compensation would be payable when he signed a contract with another club,<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/features.php?Psection_id=8&Psub_section_id=22&news_id=3490 
|title=What's happening at Kingsmeadow - feature number 4 
|publisher=[[AFC Wimbledon]] 
|date=6 June 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
but he would be allowed to play on non-contract terms, and in September 2008 he rejoined Harrow Borough on such a basis, with a view to regaining fitness following a summer operation.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news.php?Psection_id=2&Psub_section_id=2&op=archive&monthID=8&yearID=2008 
|title=Archived news: September 2008: Robin Shroot 
|publisher=[[AFC Wimbledon]] 
|date=19 September 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
At Harrow he was reunited with player-coach [[Jamie Lawrence]], with whom he had worked for three years at Lawrence's [[Tooting]] academy for [[semi-professional]] footballers.<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.southlondon-today.co.uk/tn/Sport.cfm?id=354&headline=Former 
|title=Former Premier League star backs Shroot for top 
|first=John |last=Stanton 
|work=South London Press 
|date=8 January 2009 |accessdate=8 January 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.harrowobserver.co.uk/west-london-sport/west-london-local-football/2009/01/08/former-harrow-borough-star-robin-shroot-reveals-why-birmingham-city-was-the-club-for-him-116451-22646693/ 
|title=Former Harrow Borough star Robin Shroot reveals why Birmingham City was the club for him 
|first=Tim |last=Edwards 
|work=Harrow Observer 
|date=8 January 2009 |accessdate=8 January 2009}}</ref>
Though he failed to score in his first four games back with Harrow, he followed up with nine goals in eight league games,<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.harrowboro.com/squad.php?id=121&t2=Y 
|title=Player Profile: Robin Shroot 
|publisher=[[Harrow Borough F.C.]] 
|accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
performances which attracted interest from potential purchasers and attention from opposition defenders alike.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.harrowboro.com/content.php?type=news&id=479 
|title=Manager's Notes 
|publisher=[[Harrow Borough F.C.]] 
|date=11 December 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>

In mid-December 2008, Shroot had a trial with [[Football League Championship]] club [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]]; he trained with the first-team group and scored in a friendly against [[Cheltenham Town F.C.|Cheltenham Town]].<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.birminghampost.net/midlands-birmingham-sport/west-midlands-sports/birmingham-city-fc/2008/12/19/birmingham-city-land-jordi-lopez-until-end-of-season-65233-22514171/ 
|title=Birmingham City land Jordi Lopez until end of season 
|work=[[Birmingham Post]] 
|first=Colin |last=Tattum 
|date=19 December 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.birminghampost.net/midlands-birmingham-sport/west-midlands-sports/birmingham-city-fc/2008/12/31/birmingham-city-agree-fee-for-robin-shroot-65233-22582584/ 
|title=Birmingham City agree fee for Robin Shroot 
|work=[[Birmingham Post]] 
|first=Colin |last=Tattum 
|date=31 December 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
Harrow manager, former Birmingham player [[David Howell]], was unhappy about the motives of the player's agent, suggesting he wanted "to put Robin out there for the highest bidder".<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.harrowobserver.co.uk/west-london-sport/west-london-local-football/2008/12/18/robin-shroot-to-become-a-birmingham-city-blue-116451-22504993/ 
|title=Robin Shroot to become a Birmingham City blue 
|work=[[Harrow Observer]] |publisher=Trinity Mirror Southern 
|first=Tim |last=Edwards 
|date=18 December 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>
Nevertheless, Shroot joined Birmingham on 2 January 2009, signing a two-and-a-half year contract with a one-year option,<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.blues.premiumtv.co.uk/page/News/NewsDetail/0,,10412~1504664,00.html 
|title=Big Eck's Shroot-ing Star 
|publisher=[[Birmingham City F.C]] 
|date=2 January 2009 |accessdate=2 January 2009}}</ref>
for what was described as a "nominal" fee.<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.birminghammail.net/birmingham-sport/birmingham-city-fc/birmingham-city-fc-news/2009/01/02/birmingham-city-complete-signing-of-robin-shroot-for-nominal-fee-65233-22595422/ 
|title=Birmingham City complete signing of Robin Shroot for nominal fee 
|work=[[Birmingham Mail]] 
|first=Colin |last=Tattum 
|date=2 January 2009 |accessdate=2 January 2009}}</ref>

Shroot made his first-team debut on 13 January 2009, playing the whole of the [[FA Cup]] third round defeat to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/fa_cup/7815376.stm 
|title=Birmingham 0<U+2013>2 Wolves 
|publisher=[[BBC Sport]] 
|accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref>

==International career==
Shroot qualifies to play international football for [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] because his grandmother is from that country. While still a youngster at Wimbledon, he wrote to then manager [[Lawrie Sanchez]] to tell him his international ambitions lay with Northern Ireland. He has been [[cap (sports)|cap]]ped at under-19 and under-20 level,<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/irish/6427007.stm 
|title=Shroot receives Under-20s call-up 
|publisher=[[BBC Sport]] 
|date=7 March 2007 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref> and played in the side which reached the final of the [[Milk Cup]] Elite section in 2007.<ref>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/irelands-saturday-night/news-results/millars-boys-left-crushed-by-israel-13888181.html 
|title=Millar's boys left crushed by Israel 
|work=[[Belfast Telegraph]] 
|first=Grant |last=Cameron 
|date=6 August 2007 |accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref>
Shroot's debut for [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|the under-21s]] came in November 2008 when he played the first half of a 3&ndash;1 defeat of their [[Scotland national under-21 football team|Scottish counterparts]] in November 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishfa.com/the-ifa/news/4386/u21-squad-named-for-scotland-game/ 
|title=U21 Squad Named For Scotland Game 
|publisher=[[Irish Football Association]] 
|date=6 November 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishfa.com/international-matches/match-reports/251/scotland-v-northern-ireland-cashback-international-challenge-match/ 
|title=McQuoid Double Sinks Scots 
|publisher=[[Irish Football Association]] 
|date=18 November 2008 |accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Before his move to Birmingham, Shroot had [[coach (sports)|coach]]ed at a South London junior club, Balham Blazers, and managed their under-13 side.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.balhamblazers.org.uk/clubpersonnel.htm 
|title=Club Personnel 
|publisher=Balham Blazers F.C. 
|accessdate=31 December 2008}}</ref> He intended to maintain his involvement with the club when his Birmingham commitments permitted.<ref name=Mercury20090110>{{cite news 
|url=http://www.sundaymercury.net/midlands-sport/birmingham-city-fc/birmingham-city-fc-news/2009/01/10/grass-shroots-it-s-all-about-sunday-morning-soccer-for-new-birmingham-city-signing-66331-22665553/ 
|title=Grass Shroots: It's all about Sunday morning soccer for new Birmingham City signing 
|work=[[Sunday Mercury]] |location=Birmingham 
|first=Andy |last=Walker 
|date=10 January 2009 |accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.balhamblazers.org.uk/news.htm 
|title=Shroot Signs For Birmingham 
|publisher=Balham Blazers F.C. 
|accessdate=14 January 2009}}</ref>

